# The same invalid escape `\ ` in an f-string's LITERAL part -- a separate lexer
# path in tychoc0 (the f"..." scanner) that had the identical fail-open gap. tychoc
# rejects it; tychoc0 now does too. (A bad escape in a string INSIDE an f-string
# hole already rejected in both -- the hole re-lexes through the regular string
# path -- so this locks the literal-part path specifically.)
fn main():
    x := 1
    println(f"oops\ {x}")
